claim.claim-text:
25. A system for conducting an online information service, the system comprising:
at least one processor operatively connected to a memory, wherein the processor is configured to execute system components from the memory;
a generation component configured to permit a creation of at least one respective observation generated by at least one respective user from a plurality of users, wherein the plurality of users include at least content generating users and information consumer users;
a display component configured to display to at least one other user the at least one observation;
a collection component configured to accept an opinion of the at least one other user regarding the at least one observation submitted by the at least one user; and
a control component configured to control access to at least one of the at least one observation generated by the at least one user and any collected opinions regarding the at least one observation, wherein the control component is further configured to:
restrict access by at least one information consumer to at least one of the at least one observation generated by the at least one user and any of the collected opinions regarding the at least one observation; and
permit access by the at least one information consumer to at least one of the at least one observation generated by the at least one user and any of the collected opinions in response to receiving payment from the at least one information consumer for access.
